title: Date.parse()
description: The `Date.parse()` static JS method parses a date string and returns the number of milliseconds since January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 UTC.
content: The static method that parses a date string and returns the number of milliseconds since January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 UTC (the Unix Epoch). It converts a date string into a timestamp that can be used to create or manipulate `Date` objects.
